{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KHSs4eiM6r1cLQyB691iqM","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Task Board\n2\t\n3\t## Directions (Long-term Goals - Set by Lord Only)\n4\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n5\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n6\t| D001 | Build profitable Kalshi trading operation | Trade on Kalshi.com prediction markets — find edge, build models, make money | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | kalshi.com — CFTC-regulated prediction market exchange |\n7\t| D002 | Develop data-driven trading strategies | Identify market mispricings vs real-world probability across econ, politics, crypto, weather | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | API docs: trading-api.readme.io/reference/getting-started |\n8\t| D003 | Track P&L and iterate fast | Define position sizing rules, measure strategy performance, kill losers, scale winners | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-02 | 2026-04-02 | Start with paper trading, then real capital |\n9\t| D004 | Build Kalshi Arbitrage Engine (Wen Zhou) | **PHASE 1: Market Filtering (Daily Scan).** Filter Kalshi markets by: (1) Volume ≥10,000 (exclude low-liquidity noise), (2) YES/NO ratio targets: 15-30% or 70-85% (mispriced range). Reject middle 40-60% (too efficient, no edge). Reject extremes 0-15% & 85-100% (distorted pricing). Rationale: Extreme ratios have unrealistic implied probabilities; middle range reflects consensus (no inefficiency). Output: filtered market list for Phase 2. **PHASE 2: LLM-Based Clustering (Daily Scan).** Use LLM embeddings to identify hidden market correlations. Group similar markets (e.g., Bitcoin $100k + Ethereum $5k + Crypto dominance all cluster together). Find markets with strong semantic/causal links that traditional screening misses. Output: market clusters for Phase 3. **PHASE 3: Pearson Pairwise Correlation Detection (Daily Scan).** Apply Pearson/distance-based algorithm (ref: hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab) to detect strongly correlated market pairs. Identify mispricings: if BTC moves +5% in backtest but only +2% in live, that's arbitrage. Calculate expected spread from historical correlation. Score confidence. Output: correlation_pairs.json with arbitrage candidates. **PHASE 4: C++ High-Frequency Execution (Real-Time).** Why C++: Each trade moves prices; we need sub-millisecond execution to capture arbitrage before it reverts. Algorithm: (1) Detect spread gap between correlated markets, (2) Calculate theoretical fair spread, (3) Execute buy/sell pairs to lock profit, (4) Monitor until convergence. No Python delays. No GIL. Pure performance. **Why This Works:** Phases 1-3 reduce noise (99% of markets ignored), find real edges via correlation-based pairs (harder to game than single-market signals), Phase 4 captures spread before reversion. This is the real edge. Reference: https://hudson-and-thames-arbitragelab.readthedocs-hosted.com/en/latest/distance_approach/pearson_approach.html | high | all | undefined | open | 2026-04-03 | 2026-04-03 | Wen Zhou strategy — full 4-phase pipeline. Phases 1-3 = daily batch. Phase 4 = real-time. Blocks live trading pending T236 (API credentials). |\n10\t\n11\t## Instructions (Persistent Context - Always Consider)\n12\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n13\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---------|-------|\n14\t| I001 | Token-efficient ops: grep tasks, avoid full-file reads | undefined | undefined | all | undefined | open | undefined | undefined | See CLAUDE.md |\n15\t\n16\t## Tasks (Regular Work - Assignable & Completable)\n17\t| ID | Title | Description | Priority | Group | Assignee | Status | Created | Updated | Notes |\n18\t|----|-------|-------------|----------|-------|----------|--------|---------|---